b'' b'not necessarily a thrid-party adapter; apple does manufacture transceivers' b'for thinwire and 10baset (twisted pair) cable media, as well as an aui' b'(attachment unit interface) transciever. they run at each. if you use' b"thinwire or 10baset, you'll probably also need terminators (apple's" b'transceivers are self-terminated, if i remember correctly, but i have no' b'idea about decs).' b'' b'the third-party media adapters are usually cheaper (at least in toronto) than' b"apple's. i bought the adapters from asante instead of apple." b'' b' the decstation models and come with thinwire only' b"(can't say for certain about the models and so your best bet" b'' b"that's not true. only the decstation comes with a thinwire" b'(bnc, coaxial) ethernet connector. the and b'all have a single 15-pin aui ethernet connector only. i distinctly' b'remembered this because when got the first and i thought all' b'of them are going to be thinwire. i eventually had to go back and ordered' b"destas (dec's oversized version of an aui-to-bnc adapter that must be used" b'with a transciever cable) for the rest of the stations.' b'' b'my advise to the very original poster (beverly?) is:' b'' b"(1) if all you want is to create a lan with two workstations and won't add" b'machines to it ever, go for thinwire regardless of the media type. going' b'for utp (unshielded twisted pair) wiring requires a concentrator which' b'means extra money and i believe these units come with at least ports.' b"as for thicknet, it's a nightmare and cabling is expensive. avoid it" b'unless you have no choice (e.g. the two machines are two floors parts).' b'' b'(2) on the mac side, you will need:' b'- one thinwire media adapter (from apple or third-party).' b"- macx (make sure you get version won't run on system b'- mactcp (which comes with macx; if you get macx v1.2, you should be' b"getting mactcp v1.1.1 with it. don't use earlier versions on a centris)." b'- you may or may not need a 25ohm terminator depending on the' b'thinwire media adapter. so just ask the sales if the adapter is' b'self-terminated or not.' b'- configure mactcp to use "ethernet".' b'' b'(3) on the decstation side, you will need:' b'- for a model you will only need a t-connector.' b'- for models you will need an aui-to-bnc adapter.' b'get one that can be plugged in directly to the aui port of the' b'decstation. this way you save the cost of a transciever cable' b'(a 15-pin aui male to a 15-pin aui female cable).' b'- get a 25ohm terminator.' b'' b'your two-machine network will look like this:' b'' b'' b'##t----------------------------------------------[]' b'+-----+ b'| b'+-----+ b'| b'+-----+' b'decstation centris' b'5000/200 b'or' b'' b'##t----------------------------------------------[]' b'{=} b'+-----+ b'| b'+-----+ b'+-----+' b'decstation centris' b'5000/25,125,133,240 b'' b'## 25ohm terminator' b't t connector' b'--- thinwire (rg58 coaxial cable)' b'{=} aui-to-bnc (i.e. thick-to-thin) adapter' b'[] thickwire media adapter (assuming self-terminated)' b'|' b'|' b'' b'andy' b'--' b'computing coordinator ontario, canada. m5s 1a4' b'department of industrial engineering phone: b'university of toronto fax: 